HEADWORD: Antiperistaltic
<hw>An`ti*per`i*stal"tic</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*p⟦ecr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*st⟦acr⟧l"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Opposed to, or checking motion; acting upward; --
applied to an inverted action of the intestinal tube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

